{"id":"61","name":"happy-hour-that-is-messed-up","title":"Happy Hour: That Is Messed Up","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2008-05-14T17:00:00-05:00","tags":["alternative high school initiative","department of justice","Nashville","rabies","tennessee","that is messed up"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/1415318312_321f19d8c6.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-62\" title=\"1415318312_321f19d8c6\" src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/1415318312_321f19d8c6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\"></a></p><ul><li>Williamson County&#x2019;s got rabies. Well, at least one critter does. Police confirmed a case of rabies in a skunk near the College Grove area. If you&#x2019;re out in Williamson, it may be a good idea to pull your pets inside until we hear more. [<a href=\"http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8321401\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.newschannel5.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WTVF</a>]</li><li>The U.S. Department of Justice is looking into Metro City Council&#x2019;s decision to exclude rehab centers from certain zoning districts around town, forcing one center&#x2013;Teen Challenge&#x2013;to close its doors. There&#x2019;s talk of a nasty lawsuit brewing, but the Metro&#x2019;s legal council has advised them to stay the course. [<a href=\"http://www.nashvillecitypaper.com/news.php?viewStory=60198\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">City Paper]</a></li><li>Remember when we said we weren&#x2019;t sure what the Alternative High School Initiative was? City Paper has a pretty thorough explanation of it. It looks neat, but probably not neat enough to save Metro Public Schools from The Giant Claws of Death (you know, the state government takeover.) [<a href=\"http://www.nashvillecitypaper.com/news.php?viewStory=60202\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">City Paper</a>]</li><li>We hate to leave you with this one, but we just couldn&#x2019;t resist: WKRN is reporting that some Nashville neighborhood has been overrun by &#x201C;rats, feces.&#x201D; Gross! Good news is, we found a new (for us) blog! From WKRN, we bring you <a href=\"http://www.thatismessedup.com\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.thatismessedup.com&apos;]);\">That Is Messed Up</a>. [<a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=8312142\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">WKRN</a>]</li></ul><p>